# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: runtime
domain: builder
scope: builder.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines core runtime handling for builder.

## runtime_scope
Runtime covers build draft visibility,
validation state,
approval state,
execution state,
completion/failure state,
and safe failure rendering.

## current_view_state
Runtime-visible builder state must distinguish:
- draft build
- validated build
- approved build
- executing build
- failed build
- completed build
- historical build

## validation_rules
- builder identity must resolve
- template/config basis must resolve
- actor authority must resolve
- target boundary must be valid
- execution mode must be valid

## failure_modes
- invalid template/config basis
- invalid actor authority
- invalid target boundary
- invalid execution mode
- safe runtime fallback

## observability
Runtime must emit enough signals
to distinguish validation,
approval,
execution,
completion/failure,
and failure surface.

## review_checklist
- builder runtime states are explicit
- execution-aware runtime is explicit
- failure handling is explicit
